00:00:01.468 --> 00:00:03.570 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>Previously on</i>
Dance Moms...

00:00:03.636 --> 00:00:04.471 line:5%,start
Uh-oh.

00:00:04.537 --> 00:00:06.072 line:5%,start
(gasps) She just
twisted her ankle.

00:00:06.139 --> 00:00:07.907 line:5%,start
If it gets worse,
we have to pull her.

00:00:07.974 --> 00:00:09.542 line:5%,start
Everybody else
has to learn to adjust.

00:00:09.609 --> 00:00:10.877 line:5%,start
I think that's what
she's afraid of.

00:00:10.944 --> 00:00:13.313 line:5%,start
We're talking about
what you enable to happen.

00:00:13.380 --> 00:00:14.714 line:5%,start
I don't want to dance
here anymore, Maddie.

00:00:14.781 --> 00:00:15.782 line:5%,start
I'm sick of it.

00:00:15.849 --> 00:00:18.084 line:5%,start
Melissa plays
the "I'm so nice" part,

00:00:18.151 --> 00:00:20.653 line:5%,start
and she's the sneakiest,
most underhanded person of them all.

00:00:20.720 --> 00:00:23.556 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>I'm sitting in my seat</i>
<i>watching Chloe on stage.</i>

00:00:23.623 --> 00:00:25.191 line:5%,start
<i>Boom, forgets another part.</i>

00:00:25.258 --> 00:00:28.428 line:5%,start
Don't set them
up to be okay to fail.

00:00:30.930 --> 00:00:32.332 line:5%,start
Coming up on <i>Dance Moms...</i>

00:00:32.399 --> 00:00:33.933 line:5%,start
We are here in New York City.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.536 line:5%,start
You're going to be going to
the Joffrey Ballet School.

00:00:36.603 --> 00:00:37.937 line:5%,start
You guys need to fight for this.

00:00:38.004 --> 00:00:39.406 line:5%,start
(indistinct chatter)

00:00:39.472 --> 00:00:40.440 line:5%,start
Don't you hear it?

00:00:42.075 --> 00:00:42.976 line:5%,start
Hi!

00:00:44.277 --> 00:00:46.112 line:5%,start
ABBY: This is about your kid
having an audition tomorrow

00:00:46.179 --> 00:00:47.380 line:5%,start
and her brain
not being in her head.

00:00:47.447 --> 00:00:49.282 line:5%,start
You don't respect me
and you don't respect these girls.

00:00:49.349 --> 00:00:51.684 line:5%,start
-CATHY: Talk to her as well.
-You've just got to now focus, please.

00:00:51.751 --> 00:00:52.619 line:5%,start
(door closes)

00:00:52.685 --> 00:00:55.488 line:5%,start
ABBY: My entire reputation
is humiliated.

00:00:55.555 --> 00:00:56.623 line:5%,start
Shh, shh, shh.

00:00:56.689 --> 00:00:57.824 line:5%,start
Abby's going to hate me.

00:00:57.891 --> 00:00:59.826 line:5%,start
Your kids and fine without me.

00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:03.229 line:95%,end
(theme music playing)

00:01:03.296 --> 00:01:04.831 line:95%,end
SINGER: <i>âª Get up âª</i>

00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:06.833 line:95%,end
<i>âª Get on the floor âª</i>

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:09.903 line:95%,end
<i>âª My world is with my girls âª</i>

00:01:09.969 --> 00:01:12.072 line:95%,end
<i>âª Living on the dance floor âª</i>

00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:16.076 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:01:17.477 --> 00:01:19.345 line:5%,start
ABBY: All right, here we are.

00:01:19.412 --> 00:01:20.713 line:95%,end
Let's go.

00:01:20.780 --> 00:01:22.482 line:95%,end
<i>This week the girls and I</i>
<i>are in New York City</i>

00:01:22.549 --> 00:01:25.218 line:5%,start
to rehearse
for a Joffrey Ballet audition.

00:01:25.718 --> 00:01:27.487 line:95%,end
Come on, ladies.
Let's go.

00:01:28.188 --> 00:01:30.990 line:95%,end
<i>For these little girls,</i>
<i>this is a chance of a lifetime.</i>

00:01:31.057 --> 00:01:33.159 line:95%,end
<i>I don't want to see</i>
<i>any of them blow it.</i>

00:01:33.226 --> 00:01:36.229 line:95%,end
<i>This competition season</i>
<i>has been extremely tough</i>

00:01:36.296 --> 00:01:37.764 line:95%,end
<i>and extremely rewarding,</i>

00:01:37.831 --> 00:01:39.099 line:95%,end
<i>but I think the kids are ready</i>

00:01:39.165 --> 00:01:41.701 line:95%,end
<i>for whatever</i>
<i>New York City has to offer.</i>

00:01:41.768 --> 00:01:43.603 line:95%,end
They want to show
their own talents

00:01:43.670 --> 00:01:45.939 line:95%,end
and I think this is
a great opportunity.

00:01:46.005 --> 00:01:48.374 line:95%,end
Girls, this is the big time.

00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:50.677 line:95%,end
We are here in New York City

00:01:50.743 --> 00:01:54.447 line:95%,end
in the dance Mecca
of the world right here.

00:01:54.514 --> 00:01:56.149 line:95%,end
And I want you
to take it all in.

00:01:56.216 --> 00:01:58.384 line:95%,end
Everybody you pass
on that street

00:01:59.085 --> 00:02:02.088 line:95%,end
probably took a dance lesson
at some point in their life.

00:02:02.155 --> 00:02:03.356 line:95%,end
Do you understand that?

00:02:03.423 --> 00:02:05.558 line:95%,end
Yes, there's a lot of kids
that win competitions,

00:02:05.625 --> 00:02:07.961 line:95%,end
a lot of kids who get crowns
on their heads,

00:02:08.027 --> 00:02:10.864 line:95%,end
and there's a handful
that make it in the industry.

00:02:12.065 --> 00:02:13.032 line:95%,end
Remember that.

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.735 line:95%,end
I want to talk about
Michigan first.

00:02:15.802 --> 00:02:18.571 line:95%,end
We are not going to win
a group dance

00:02:18.638 --> 00:02:23.042 line:95%,end
until everybody in this group
is on the same level.

00:02:23.409 --> 00:02:26.112 line:5%,start
PRESENTER: <i>Number (indistinct) 1A,</i>
<i>"Wipe Them Out,"</i>

00:02:26.179 --> 00:02:27.914 line:5%,start
<i>Star Dance Studio.</i>

00:02:28.281 --> 00:02:31.251 line:95%,end
When parts of the choreography
are in unison,

00:02:31.317 --> 00:02:32.819 line:95%,end
you all need to be in unison.

00:02:32.886 --> 00:02:33.720 line:95%,end
That's what it means.

00:02:33.786 --> 00:02:35.588 line:95%,end
<i>Last week,</i>
<i>these girls lost again.</i>

00:02:35.655 --> 00:02:36.990 line:95%,end
<i>They were sloppy.</i>

00:02:37.056 --> 00:02:38.224 line:95%,end
<i>Their timing was off.</i>

00:02:38.291 --> 00:02:39.893 line:95%,end
<i>They need to bond as a group.</i>

00:02:39.959 --> 00:02:42.529 line:95%,end
It's not always
about your solos.

00:02:42.595 --> 00:02:44.197 line:95%,end
It's about that group,

00:02:44.264 --> 00:02:45.598 line:95%,end
and you need
to learn the dance in a group.

00:02:45.665 --> 00:02:47.700 line:95%,end
If you don't apply
the corrections,

00:02:48.434 --> 00:02:49.903 line:95%,end
you're not going to improve.

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:51.738 line:95%,end
And that's the issue.

00:02:51.804 --> 00:02:53.339 line:95%,end
<i>Until they realize that,</i>

00:02:54.207 --> 00:02:55.608 line:95%,end
it's not going to happen.

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:57.644 line:95%,end
Now, on with the pyramid.

00:02:57.710 --> 00:02:59.812 line:5%,start
Luckily the pyramid
found its way to Manhattan.

00:02:59.879 --> 00:03:00.847 line:5%,start
Yay.

00:03:00.914 --> 00:03:02.115 line:95%,end
On the bottom
of the pyramid...

00:03:03.283 --> 00:03:04.250 line:95%,end
is Paige.

00:03:04.317 --> 00:03:05.652 line:95%,end
Did you correct the arms?

00:03:05.718 --> 00:03:06.686 line:95%,end
Yes.

00:03:07.253 --> 00:03:08.621 line:95%,end
Did you put the phone away?

00:03:09.088 --> 00:03:09.989 line:95%,end
No.

00:03:10.056 --> 00:03:13.793 line:95%,end
She gets no credit for doing
her back tuck or her press or--

00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:15.428 line:95%,end
-Credit?
-It's her phone.

00:03:16.129 --> 00:03:18.131 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I thought watching</i>
<i>Paige in the group number,</i>

00:03:18.198 --> 00:03:19.165 line:95%,end
<i>I thought she did great.</i>

00:03:19.232 --> 00:03:21.501 line:5%,start
I just don't think that Abby
gives her enough credit.

00:03:21.568 --> 00:03:22.835 line:95%,end
<i>She always sticks her</i>
<i>in the back</i>

00:03:22.902 --> 00:03:24.404 line:95%,end
<i>and doesn't pay</i>
<i>attention to her,</i>

00:03:24.470 --> 00:03:26.272 line:95%,end
<i>and I think</i>
<i>she can hold her own.</i>


00:03:26.339 --> 00:03:29.576 line:95%,end
I think she's fine in the group.

00:03:29.642 --> 00:03:30.510 line:95%,end
ABBY: Next,

00:03:31.778 --> 00:03:32.879 line:95%,end
Mackenzie.

00:03:32.946 --> 00:03:37.150 line:95%,end
You can improv if you're early
on the music in a solo.

00:03:37.217 --> 00:03:39.018 line:95%,end
But when you do it in a trio

00:03:39.085 --> 00:03:40.453 line:95%,end
and you don't tell
the other two partners

00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:42.155 line:95%,end
to do it ahead of time,

00:03:42.222 --> 00:03:44.023 line:95%,end
you make them look like idiots
because you were out there,

00:03:44.090 --> 00:03:45.592 line:95%,end
woo, shaking it up.

00:03:45.658 --> 00:03:46.659 line:95%,end
Understood?

00:03:48.861 --> 00:03:50.630 line:95%,end
Next, Chloe.

00:03:51.197 --> 00:03:52.332 line:95%,end
Time to face the music.

00:03:52.932 --> 00:03:53.833 line:95%,end
Forgot your routine.

00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:58.938 line:95%,end
SINGER: <i>âª Remain</i>
<i>when watercolors fade âª</i>

00:03:59.005 --> 00:04:00.440 line:95%,end
You're not seven anymore.

00:04:00.506 --> 00:04:01.441 line:95%,end
You're 10 years old.

00:04:01.507 --> 00:04:03.843 line:95%,end
You can't make up
your own thing and wait to get back

00:04:03.910 --> 00:04:06.246 line:95%,end
onto the music
when 35 other dancers

00:04:06.312 --> 00:04:07.547 line:95%,end
are doing the right thing.

00:04:08.214 --> 00:04:09.382 line:95%,end
That's a pink slip.

00:04:09.449 --> 00:04:10.917 line:95%,end
That's the unemployment line.

00:04:10.984 --> 00:04:12.118 line:95%,end
Understood?

00:04:13.219 --> 00:04:15.755 line:95%,end
Next, Nia.

00:04:15.822 --> 00:04:16.956 line:95%,end
You hurt your foot.

00:04:17.023 --> 00:04:18.324 line:95%,end
You worked through it.

00:04:18.391 --> 00:04:19.692 line:95%,end
It all worked out.

00:04:19.759 --> 00:04:21.761 line:95%,end
However, it's the technique.

00:04:21.828 --> 00:04:24.797 line:95%,end
And it's like we tell you
over and over, it's up to you.

00:04:24.864 --> 00:04:26.899 line:95%,end
Do you want to fix it?
Do you want to make it better?

00:04:26.966 --> 00:04:27.800 line:95%,end
Then you will.

00:04:28.668 --> 00:04:29.569 line:95%,end
Understood?

00:04:30.737 --> 00:04:33.206 line:95%,end
Next, we have Brooke.

00:04:33.273 --> 00:04:35.975 line:95%,end
Brooke, you did
what you needed to do.

00:04:36.042 --> 00:04:38.945 line:95%,end
But you always just do
what you needed to do.

00:04:39.012 --> 00:04:40.513 line:95%,end
I want to see more from you.

00:04:40.580 --> 00:04:41.447 line:5%,start
I'd love to give her more,

00:04:41.514 --> 00:04:43.516 line:5%,start
but Miss Abby spends all her time
with all the other girls.

00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:48.288 line:95%,end
And on top again is Maddie.

00:04:48.354 --> 00:04:51.557 line:95%,end
I challenge you
to keep winning your solos

00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:53.226 line:95%,end
because you pick up quickly.

00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:54.494 line:95%,end
MELISSA: <i>No big surprise.</i>

00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:55.662 line:95%,end
<i>For the fifth week in a row,</i>

00:04:55.728 --> 00:04:57.530 line:95%,end
Maddie reigns supreme
at the top of the pyramid.

00:04:57.597 --> 00:04:59.866 line:95%,end
I want to talk about
after the competition.

00:05:00.500 --> 00:05:03.303 line:95%,end
The scout from
the Joffrey Ballet School

00:05:03.369 --> 00:05:05.305 line:95%,end
came to our dressing room.

00:05:05.371 --> 00:05:07.940 line:95%,end
They chose
the Abby Lee Dance Company.

00:05:08.007 --> 00:05:11.010 line:95%,end
<i>The Joffrey Ballet School</i>
<i>has huge history here.</i>

00:05:11.077 --> 00:05:14.647 line:95%,end
Robert Joffrey started
the school in 1953.

00:05:14.714 --> 00:05:17.917 line:95%,end
<i>There are people from all over</i>
<i>the world coming here to train.</i>

00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:20.620 line:95%,end
You're going to be going
to the Joffrey School

00:05:20.687 --> 00:05:22.622 line:95%,end
with some of the most
prestigious instructors

00:05:22.689 --> 00:05:23.623 line:95%,end
in all of New York.

00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:24.857 line:95%,end
<i>Throughout the year,</i>

00:05:24.924 --> 00:05:28.194 line:95%,end
Joffrey auditions
over 20,000 dancers

00:05:28.261 --> 00:05:30.330 line:95%,end
for their Summer Intensive program,

00:05:30.930 --> 00:05:33.866 line:95%,end
and they only give
a handful of scholarships away.

00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:36.969 line:95%,end
If one of my girls
would get those scholarships,

00:05:37.036 --> 00:05:39.405 line:95%,end
that would just be
another feather in my cap.

00:05:39.472 --> 00:05:40.673 line:95%,end
The judges
that are judging you

00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:43.042 line:95%,end
are three instructors
at the Joffrey School.

00:05:43.109 --> 00:05:45.178 line:95%,end
They're going to look at feet,

00:05:45.244 --> 00:05:47.447 line:95%,end
turnout, body lines.

00:05:47.513 --> 00:05:49.949 line:95%,end
Everything you've learned
up until this point

00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:52.185 line:95%,end
is going to come
into play in this audition.

00:05:52.251 --> 00:05:53.986 line:95%,end
MELISSA: <i>I have to tell you</i>
<i>that I'm very nervous</i>

00:05:54.053 --> 00:05:58.057 line:95%,end
<i>for our girls to be auditioning</i>
<i>for the Joffrey Ballet School</i>

00:05:58.124 --> 00:06:01.527 line:5%,start
simply because our girls
don't get a lot of ballet anymore,

00:06:01.594 --> 00:06:04.931 line:95%,end
so I hope that they don't
embarrass themselves.

00:06:04.997 --> 00:06:06.232 line:95%,end
You guys need to fight for this.

00:06:06.833 --> 00:06:09.335 line:95%,end
We have to work
on a ballet combination today.

00:06:09.736 --> 00:06:13.339 line:95%,end
We have to work on
a short presentation

00:06:13.406 --> 00:06:15.875 line:95%,end
for each one of you to do
when you go into that audition.

00:06:15.942 --> 00:06:18.044 line:95%,end
I expected you
to look like ballerinas.

00:06:19.011 --> 00:06:20.446 line:95%,end
I'm shocked at the way
you're dressed.

00:06:20.513 --> 00:06:22.749 line:95%,end
Here you are in New York City

00:06:22.815 --> 00:06:25.118 line:95%,end
going to a professional dance studio.

00:06:25.184 --> 00:06:27.186 line:95%,end
You never know
who's going to be there.

00:06:27.253 --> 00:06:28.821 line:95%,end
You never know
who's going to see you.

00:06:29.756 --> 00:06:31.290 line:95%,end
You always want
to look your best.

00:06:31.357 --> 00:06:33.760 line:95%,end
You're going to have
a pinks tights on.

00:06:33.826 --> 00:06:35.261 line:95%,end
You're going to have a leotard on.

00:06:35.328 --> 00:06:37.130 line:95%,end
You're going to have
your hair in a bun.

00:06:37.196 --> 00:06:39.365 line:95%,end
So moms, you're going
to have to go out,

00:06:39.432 --> 00:06:41.234 line:95%,end
you're going to have
to hit the dance wear store,

00:06:41.300 --> 00:06:43.269 line:95%,end
and I want them looking
like ballerinas.

00:06:43.336 --> 00:06:44.470 line:95%,end
The look is half the battle.

00:06:44.537 --> 00:06:45.938 line:95%,end
Mommy's not going to be there.

00:06:46.539 --> 00:06:48.474 line:95%,end
Abby's not going to be in there.

00:06:48.541 --> 00:06:49.776 line:95%,end
It's you.

00:06:49.842 --> 00:06:51.544 line:95%,end
You either sink or swim.


00:06:52.712 --> 00:06:54.147 line:95%,end
And please don't embarrass me.

00:06:54.981 --> 00:06:56.349 line:95%,end
CHLOE: <i>It's a really big deal</i>

00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:57.950 line:95%,end
<i>to dance at the Joffrey Ballet School,</i>

00:06:58.017 --> 00:06:58.985 line:95%,end
<i>especially when you're young.</i>

00:06:59.051 --> 00:07:01.888 line:5%,start
Performing for a huge audience

00:07:01.954 --> 00:07:04.190 line:5%,start
actually doesn't really get me
that nervous,

00:07:04.257 --> 00:07:06.392 line:95%,end
<i>but performing for like three of--</i>

00:07:06.459 --> 00:07:08.828 line:95%,end
like amazing ballerinas, it's--

00:07:08.895 --> 00:07:10.930 line:95%,end
that's a little nerve-racking.

00:07:10.997 --> 00:07:12.665 line:95%,end
ABBY: In addition to our rehearsals

00:07:12.732 --> 00:07:14.066 line:95%,end
for this ballet audition,

00:07:14.133 --> 00:07:16.803 line:95%,end
we are also going
to be working on a number.

00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:18.604 line:95%,end
You heard that right.

00:07:19.105 --> 00:07:23.042 line:95%,end
So we will be attending
Starbound Competition

00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:25.077 line:95%,end
in Paramus, New Jersey.

00:07:26.813 --> 00:07:28.948 line:95%,end
And the competition
is going to be fierce.

00:07:29.015 --> 00:07:30.683 line:95%,end
<i>I've had it with these girls.</i>

00:07:30.750 --> 00:07:32.952 line:95%,end
We are going
to Starbound this weekend

00:07:33.019 --> 00:07:34.821 line:95%,end
and they have
a reputation to uphold.

00:07:34.887 --> 00:07:37.490 line:95%,end
They are reigning
national champions.

00:07:37.557 --> 00:07:40.526 line:95%,end
I expect them to win,
and they're going to do it.

00:07:40.593 --> 00:07:43.162 line:95%,end
Ladies, our group routine this week

00:07:43.229 --> 00:07:45.264 line:95%,end
is about a very serious topic.

00:07:45.531 --> 00:07:46.365 line:95%,end
Again?

00:07:46.432 --> 00:07:50.570 line:95%,end
Let me just say,
each one of you is in jail.

00:07:51.804 --> 00:07:56.075 line:95%,end
I had a brilliant idea to do
kind of a take on

00:07:56.142 --> 00:07:59.212 line:95%,end
an old number from
the Broadway show <i>Chicago.</i>

00:07:59.278 --> 00:08:04.016 line:95%,end
<i>But I want to water it down</i>
<i>for nine, ten, eleven-year-olds.</i>

00:08:04.083 --> 00:08:05.785 line:95%,end
So they're like jailbirds.

00:08:05.852 --> 00:08:09.055 line:95%,end
It's dark,
it's a bit avant-garde,

00:08:09.121 --> 00:08:10.523 line:95%,end
and it's going to be fun.

00:08:11.524 --> 00:08:14.393 line:5%,start
It's very weird being in jail

00:08:14.460 --> 00:08:17.396 line:5%,start
because I've never been
there before.

00:08:17.997 --> 00:08:21.300 line:95%,end
Chloe, you just came off a solo.

00:08:21.367 --> 00:08:22.568 line:95%,end
You forgot your routine.

00:08:22.902 --> 00:08:24.737 line:95%,end
You got to get right
back on that horse.

00:08:24.804 --> 00:08:26.873 line:95%,end
You're going to be doing
a solo this weekend.

00:08:27.406 --> 00:08:31.410 line:95%,end
Maddie, you've been undefeated

00:08:31.477 --> 00:08:32.945 line:95%,end
for the last few weeks,

00:08:33.012 --> 00:08:34.714 line:95%,end
so I'm challenging you once again

00:08:34.780 --> 00:08:36.482 line:95%,end
to do a solo at Starbound.

