I found out
that Joffrey Ballet

00:09:15.821 --> 00:09:17.323 line:95%,end
is having open auditions

00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:20.826 line:95%,end
in my most favorite city in the world.

00:09:20.893 --> 00:09:22.128 line:95%,end
KIDS: New York.

00:09:22.194 --> 00:09:23.162 line:95%,end
New York.

00:09:23.229 --> 00:09:25.598 line:5%,start
I've got a lot of work
that I have to do.

00:09:25.665 --> 00:09:29.168 line:95%,end
<i>I think that we are completely ready</i>

00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:30.870 line:95%,end
<i>to go up against</i>

00:09:30.937 --> 00:09:32.271 line:95%,end
some of Abby's dancers

00:09:32.338 --> 00:09:35.608 line:95%,end
and audition
for a scholarship to Joffrey.

00:09:35.675 --> 00:09:37.977 line:95%,end
We're going to hit the audition,

00:09:38.044 --> 00:09:41.447 line:95%,end
and then we're
going to New Jersey

00:09:41.514 --> 00:09:43.649 line:95%,end
because Starbound is there.

00:09:43.716 --> 00:09:45.151 line:95%,end
Is Abby going to be there?

00:09:45.217 --> 00:09:47.286 line:95%,end
CATHY: Yeah, pressure's on,
Miss Kendall.

00:09:47.353 --> 00:09:50.489 line:95%,end
There's probably going to be
more and more events

00:09:50.556 --> 00:09:52.525 line:95%,end
that we run into Abby.
That's just the way it is.

00:09:52.592 --> 00:09:54.427 line:95%,end
I think that we probably
have better ballet training

00:09:54.493 --> 00:09:55.728 line:95%,end
than they do, but we'll see.

00:09:55.795 --> 00:09:58.230 line:95%,end
Abby is way stuck
in vaudeville.

00:09:58.297 --> 00:10:02.201 line:95%,end
She's still dancing
on a 1940s stage with her mom,

00:10:02.268 --> 00:10:06.472 line:95%,end
<i>and we have a wonderful routine</i>
<i>that is very heartfelt</i>

00:10:06.539 --> 00:10:09.075 line:95%,end
that I think that finally
we may be able

00:10:09.141 --> 00:10:11.043 line:95%,end
to beat Abby with this number.

00:10:11.110 --> 00:10:12.178 line:95%,end
And go.

00:10:12.244 --> 00:10:13.846 line:95%,end
One, two, three.

00:10:13.913 --> 00:10:15.381 line:95%,end
Two, two, three.

00:10:15.448 --> 00:10:16.349 line:95%,end
Boom!


00:10:17.817 --> 00:10:20.853 line:5%,start
(pensive music playing)

00:10:20.920 --> 00:10:24.056 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>Pick out something</i>
<i>from one of your solos,</i>

00:10:24.123 --> 00:10:25.658 line:5%,start
something that is amazing

00:10:25.725 --> 00:10:27.927 line:5%,start
that you do better
than anybody else does.

00:10:27.994 --> 00:10:30.262 line:5%,start
But the Abby Lee Dance Company
is going to concentrate

00:10:30.329 --> 00:10:32.164 line:5%,start
on two main things,

00:10:32.231 --> 00:10:34.300 line:95%,end
<i>the Joffrey Ballet audition,</i>

00:10:34.367 --> 00:10:37.903 line:95%,end
<i>and the very next day</i>
<i>the Starbound competition.</i>

00:10:37.970 --> 00:10:40.439 line:95%,end
I don't think that you understand quite
how important this is.

00:10:40.506 --> 00:10:42.942 line:95%,end
I mean, you cannot go in there
and look like a slacker.

00:10:43.009 --> 00:10:45.511 line:95%,end
I think just walking
into the Joffrey School

00:10:45.578 --> 00:10:47.246 line:95%,end
is going to be
tough on these kids.

00:10:47.313 --> 00:10:48.948 line:95%,end
They are not little Trinas.

00:10:49.015 --> 00:10:52.551 line:95%,end
<i>They don't take ballet class</i>
<i>every single day all day long,</i>

00:10:52.618 --> 00:10:54.587 line:95%,end
<i>so I think it's going</i>
<i>to be intimidating,</i>

00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:56.622 line:95%,end
I think they're going
to be frightened,

00:10:56.689 --> 00:10:58.524 line:95%,end
<i>I think they're going to</i>
<i>be a nervous wreck,</i>

00:10:58.591 --> 00:11:00.526 line:95%,end
<i>and I just hope</i>
<i>their mothers are frightened</i>

00:11:00.593 --> 00:11:02.328 line:95%,end
<i>and nervous and keep</i>
<i>their mouths closed.</i>

00:11:02.395 --> 00:11:04.230 line:95%,end
You're going in front of people

00:11:04.296 --> 00:11:06.132 line:95%,end
that have had great careers.

00:11:06.499 --> 00:11:09.568 line:95%,end
You don't want to walk in there
and be the big joke

00:11:09.635 --> 00:11:11.837 line:95%,end
that they're going to laugh
at when they go home tonight.

00:11:11.904 --> 00:11:13.673 line:95%,end
HOLLY: <i>Everyone feels on edge.</i>

00:11:13.739 --> 00:11:15.374 line:95%,end
<i>We have this audition coming up</i>

00:11:15.441 --> 00:11:19.011 line:5%,start
and the girls do not have
a lot of ballet background.

00:11:19.078 --> 00:11:21.313 line:95%,end
<i>There's more pressure</i>
<i>than normal this week.</i>

00:11:21.380 --> 00:11:24.383 line:95%,end
ABBY: And where do you think
an arabesque should be?

00:11:24.450 --> 00:11:26.185 line:95%,end
Down here where yours is?

00:11:27.019 --> 00:11:27.920 line:95%,end
No.

00:11:27.987 --> 00:11:29.955 line:95%,end
At least parallel to the floor.

00:11:30.656 --> 00:11:33.459 line:95%,end
And you can't do
a crash course on this.

00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:37.630 line:95%,end
No, we're not fitting all of our ballet
training in for the past two years

00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:39.398 line:95%,end
in this hour class.

00:11:40.533 --> 00:11:41.534 line:95%,end
ABBY:
How did that look?

00:11:41.600 --> 00:11:42.635 line:95%,end
-Better?
-MOMS: Uh-hmm.

00:11:43.235 --> 00:11:44.203 line:95%,end
Keep going.

00:11:44.270 --> 00:11:45.771 line:95%,end
This has to stop.

00:11:46.238 --> 00:11:47.339 line:95%,end
But it keeps falling down.

00:11:47.406 --> 00:11:50.242 line:95%,end
I know, but that's why you wear
a leotard that fits you correctly.

00:11:50.309 --> 00:11:53.579 line:95%,end
Abby, is it possible
that, um, you could give us

00:11:53.646 --> 00:11:57.049 line:95%,end
some ideas when we go to look
for the appropriate black leotard

00:11:57.116 --> 00:11:59.418 line:95%,end
if there are certain types
of leotards we should be looking for

00:11:59.485 --> 00:12:01.220 line:95%,end
that complement
each of their body styles?

00:12:01.287 --> 00:12:02.555 line:95%,end
Not saying
that we can find them,

00:12:02.621 --> 00:12:03.989 line:95%,end
but we might stand
a better chance.

00:12:04.056 --> 00:12:06.525 line:95%,end
You want your legs
to look long and your body--

00:12:06.592 --> 00:12:08.728 line:95%,end
your torso to look short.

00:12:08.794 --> 00:12:10.596 line:95%,end
This is a cute outfit
and she's wearing it

00:12:10.663 --> 00:12:12.164 line:95%,end
and it's not giving her
a problem.

00:12:12.231 --> 00:12:15.668 line:95%,end
However, this would be
more appropriate.

00:12:15.735 --> 00:12:16.736 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Wow, yeah.

00:12:16.802 --> 00:12:17.837 line:95%,end
ABBY:
Even from the side.

00:12:17.903 --> 00:12:18.871 line:95%,end
HOLLY:
I'll be honest with you.

00:12:18.938 --> 00:12:22.742 line:95%,end
I'm not really sure what
a New York City look is for a dancer,

00:12:22.808 --> 00:12:25.745 line:95%,end
<i>so if she has this vision,</i>
<i>it's her responsibility</i>

00:12:25.811 --> 00:12:27.079 line:95%,end
<i>to communicate that</i>

00:12:27.146 --> 00:12:29.248 line:95%,end
because otherwise
we can't prepare them

00:12:29.315 --> 00:12:31.550 line:95%,end
for what she has in mind.

00:12:31.617 --> 00:12:36.222 line:95%,end
All this stuff
is really taking away

00:12:36.288 --> 00:12:40.126 line:95%,end
from her dancing,
and it's all about selling that outfit.

00:12:40.192 --> 00:12:43.229 line:95%,end
All of you stop
with these crazy outfits.

00:12:45.131 --> 00:12:47.733 line:95%,end
(whimsical music playing)

00:12:48.267 --> 00:12:50.069 line:95%,end
MELISSA:
Ooh, I'm so excited!

00:12:50.703 --> 00:12:52.738 line:95%,end
I wonder if this is
a flagship store.

00:12:52.805 --> 00:12:55.341 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>If we can find</i>
<i>a way to quiet Abby down,</i>

00:12:55.407 --> 00:12:56.242 line:5%,start
let's do it.

00:12:56.308 --> 00:12:57.610 line:5%,start
Let's go shopping
for black leotards

00:12:57.676 --> 00:12:59.111 line:5%,start
so tomorrow
we don't have to hear it.

00:12:59.178 --> 00:13:03.849 line:95%,end
We're looking for black leos
that have really high cuts for kids.

00:13:03.916 --> 00:13:06.252 line:95%,end
<i>Now I'm feeling</i>
<i>a little pressured, overwhelmed.</i>

00:13:06.318 --> 00:13:08.354 line:95%,end
<i>Abby wants us</i>
<i>to get special leotards</i>

00:13:08.420 --> 00:13:10.656 line:5%,start
and we don't have any time
in the day to do so.

00:13:10.723 --> 00:13:11.857 line:95%,end
WOMAN: That's too basic?

00:13:11.924 --> 00:13:14.460 line:95%,end
-She wants something a little more--
-Well, just prettier.

00:13:14.527 --> 00:13:17.596 line:95%,end
We didn't know we were supposed
to bring 900 black leotards.

00:13:17.663 --> 00:13:18.731 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I brought two.

00:13:18.798 --> 00:13:20.633 line:95%,end
She's so particular
about what fits

00:13:20.699 --> 00:13:22.468 line:95%,end
and what doesn't and the color.

00:13:22.535 --> 00:13:25.404 line:95%,end
Do you think those leotards
are going to satisfy Abby?

00:13:25.471 --> 00:13:26.906 line:95%,end
CHRISTI:
<i>The shopping trip went well.</i>

00:13:26.972 --> 00:13:28.908 line:95%,end
<i>We were able to each find</i>
<i>a leotard for the girls.</i>


00:13:28.974 --> 00:13:29.875 line:95%,end
<i>They were solid.</i>

00:13:29.942 --> 00:13:31.677 line:95%,end
We got our pink tights
and our ballet slippers

00:13:31.744 --> 00:13:34.079 line:95%,end
so hopefully mom's
the word tomorrow.

00:13:34.146 --> 00:13:36.382 line:95%,end
You know, she's so specific
about what a leotard

00:13:36.448 --> 00:13:37.449 line:95%,end
can do for your body.

00:13:37.516 --> 00:13:39.819 line:95%,end
Maybe we ought to ask
if they have one in her size.

00:13:39.885 --> 00:13:42.221 line:95%,end
Oh, they don't make
leotards that size.

00:13:42.288 --> 00:13:44.690 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:13:46.926 --> 00:13:50.129 line:5%,start
Everybody who dances
for Candy Apples

00:13:50.196 --> 00:13:52.932 line:95%,end
knows that they have
a certain aura about them

00:13:52.998 --> 00:13:54.967 line:95%,end
when they walk into a competition.

00:13:55.034 --> 00:13:57.837 line:5%,start
Based on everything
that I've done with Kendall,

00:13:57.903 --> 00:14:00.773 line:95%,end
I think that
she is completely ready

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:03.909 line:95%,end
to go up against
some of Abby's dancers

00:14:03.976 --> 00:14:07.346 line:95%,end
and audition
for a scholarship to Joffrey.

00:14:07.413 --> 00:14:11.917 line:95%,end
You know I'm down
a spectacular dancer.

00:14:13.052 --> 00:14:15.020 line:95%,end
I broke my ankle.

00:14:15.087 --> 00:14:17.423 line:95%,end
I put a lot
of stock in Taylor

00:14:17.489 --> 00:14:20.025 line:95%,end
and I don't want to pressure you
by any means

00:14:20.092 --> 00:14:22.728 line:95%,end
other than to say
she's got big shoes to fill.

00:14:23.262 --> 00:14:27.099 line:5%,start
I'm really nervous to do my solos
in front of ballet judges

00:14:27.166 --> 00:14:30.236 line:95%,end
because I'm used to doing it
in front of audiences

00:14:30.302 --> 00:14:34.206 line:95%,end
and not just being
in a room with judges.

00:14:34.273 --> 00:14:36.442 line:95%,end
CATHY: You have
to rise to the occasion.

00:14:36.508 --> 00:14:38.711 line:95%,end
You know,
cream rises to the top.

00:14:38.777 --> 00:14:41.213 line:95%,end
So we want to have
ourselves a latte.

00:14:42.314 --> 00:14:45.251 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:14:46.051 --> 00:14:48.754 line:5%,start
When you step forward,
right away your heads forward.

00:14:48.821 --> 00:14:50.222 line:5%,start
Boom, boom, bap.

00:14:50.289 --> 00:14:52.591 line:5%,start
CHLOE: <i>I am so excited</i>
<i>for my solo this week.</i>

00:14:52.658 --> 00:14:55.227 line:5%,start
<i>I'm finally the Red Queen</i>
<i>from </i>Alice in Wonderland,

00:14:55.294 --> 00:14:57.897 line:5%,start
and I've been waiting
for this forever.

00:14:57.963 --> 00:14:59.665 line:95%,end
Take your hands
right here and go.

00:15:01.333 --> 00:15:02.635 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>Chloe is doing</i>
Queen of Hearts.

00:15:02.701 --> 00:15:05.905 line:95%,end
<i>She really relates to the darkness,</i>

00:15:06.705 --> 00:15:08.007 line:95%,end
<i>to the viciousness,</i>

00:15:08.073 --> 00:15:10.142 line:95%,end
<i>to the evil aspect</i>

00:15:10.209 --> 00:15:13.078 line:95%,end
<i>of playing a character</i>

00:15:13.145 --> 00:15:14.013 line:95%,end
that is on the dark side.

00:15:14.079 --> 00:15:17.549 line:95%,end
And when you lunge,
your head's here.

00:15:17.616 --> 00:15:19.084 line:95%,end
Push through.
Look at it.

00:15:19.151 --> 00:15:20.286 line:95%,end
Change your head around.

00:15:20.352 --> 00:15:22.821 line:95%,end
<i>You know, when you tell</i>
<i>a kid to be happy and smile,</i>

00:15:22.888 --> 00:15:23.856 line:95%,end
<i>that's easy.</i>

00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:26.158 line:95%,end
But when you tell them
that they have to be evil

00:15:26.225 --> 00:15:27.826 line:95%,end
<i>and they have to be insightful</i>

00:15:27.893 --> 00:15:30.663 line:95%,end
<i>and they have to be</i>
<i>attacking the judges,</i>

00:15:30.729 --> 00:15:32.631 line:95%,end
<i>it gives them more to work with.</i>

00:15:33.232 --> 00:15:35.401 line:95%,end
<i>It gives them</i>
<i>a story line to follow.</i>

00:15:36.135 --> 00:15:38.203 line:95%,end
And that's where Chloe shines.

00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:39.338 line:95%,end
Come on, Maddie.

00:15:40.339 --> 00:15:43.442 line:95%,end
So Maddie, it's called
"In My Heart."

00:15:43.509 --> 00:15:45.811 line:5%,start
We have one day to learn it

00:15:45.878 --> 00:15:48.147 line:5%,start
because tomorrow
is the big Joffrey Ballet audition.

00:15:48.213 --> 00:15:50.582 line:5%,start
MADDIE: My solo this week
is a lyrical routine,

00:15:50.649 --> 00:15:52.017 line:5%,start
and it's called "In My Heart,"

00:15:52.084 --> 00:15:55.054 line:5%,start
and I really love the song
and the choreography.

00:15:55.120 --> 00:15:56.388 line:95%,end
Low. Hold.

00:15:56.789 --> 00:15:58.190 line:95%,end
(makes sound)

00:15:58.257 --> 00:16:00.225 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>This is a stellar routine for her.</i>

00:16:00.292 --> 00:16:02.728 line:95%,end
<i>It has all the elements</i>
<i>that she needs.</i>

00:16:02.795 --> 00:16:04.163 line:95%,end
<i>She jumps. She turns.</i>

00:16:04.229 --> 00:16:07.199 line:95%,end
<i>Her transitions are lovely.</i>

00:16:07.266 --> 00:16:11.036 line:95%,end
It certainly is a routine
that's right up Maddie's ally.

00:16:11.103 --> 00:16:13.138 line:95%,end
That, and go right
into that from there.

00:16:15.307 --> 00:16:16.809 line:95%,end
One, two.

00:16:17.943 --> 00:16:19.144 line:95%,end
MELISSA: It's not like... perfect.

00:16:19.211 --> 00:16:20.913 line:95%,end
ABBY: And you can illusion and tilt.

00:16:20.980 --> 00:16:22.848 line:95%,end
<i>The pressure is on.</i>

00:16:22.915 --> 00:16:26.185 line:95%,end
I expect Maddie
to do really well this weekend.

00:16:26.885 --> 00:16:28.520 line:95%,end
It's hard to get to the top
of the pyramid,

00:16:28.587 --> 00:16:29.655 line:95%,end
but it's even...

00:16:29.722 --> 00:16:31.991 line:95%,end
-Harder to stay there?
-Harder to stay there.

00:16:32.057 --> 00:16:33.559 line:95%,end
So game on.


00:16:38.397 --> 00:16:41.200 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:16:41.266 --> 00:16:42.768 line:5%,start
ABBY: Girls, come on.

00:16:42.835 --> 00:16:43.802 line:5%,start
Listen up.

00:16:43.869 --> 00:16:48.607 line:5%,start
We have two days
until you are in Paramus, New Jersey

00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:50.676 line:5%,start
doing this competition in Starbound.

00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:54.880 line:5%,start
I really need my girls
to turn it on and turn it up.

00:16:54.947 --> 00:16:57.783 line:95%,end
<i>Our group number has not placed</i>
<i>in the top for weeks</i>

00:16:57.850 --> 00:16:59.151 line:95%,end
<i>and I'm sick of it.</i>

00:16:59.218 --> 00:17:01.453 line:95%,end
<i>We have a few more</i>
<i>hours to rehearse</i>

00:17:01.520 --> 00:17:04.289 line:95%,end
and they better get this perfect.

00:17:04.356 --> 00:17:07.226 line:95%,end
Go get your dance bags,
put your jazz shoes on.

00:17:07.292 --> 00:17:10.295 line:95%,end
(sighs) (bleep).
We don't even have a dance bag.

00:17:12.998 --> 00:17:14.800 line:95%,end
Go tell Miss Abby
that you and Mackenzie

00:17:14.867 --> 00:17:16.068 line:95%,end
-left them on the couch.
-I don't have my shoes.

00:17:16.135 --> 00:17:17.069 line:95%,end
Don't start crying.

00:17:17.136 --> 00:17:19.872 line:95%,end
I'm not in the mood today
for any of this at all.

00:17:20.639 --> 00:17:22.007 line:95%,end
So don't get upset about it.

00:17:22.074 --> 00:17:23.308 line:95%,end
I don't care.

00:17:23.375 --> 00:17:25.811 line:95%,end
ABBY: Girls, let's go.

00:17:25.878 --> 00:17:28.047 line:95%,end
-Come on.
-Her dance bags are at the hotel.

00:17:31.183 --> 00:17:33.852 line:95%,end
Every kid makes a mistake,
Maddie, okay?

00:17:33.919 --> 00:17:35.020 line:95%,end
You're not perfect.

